Gosh Mark - I had a tranny where that small reverse
gear disengaged from its' fork. The gear was able to
slide and engage / disengage regardless of what other
gears were engaged. If I had not had this happen to me
personally and had not had to jack the back of the bus
up high and rock the rear wheel until the gear slid
the other way, then I would not have written about it!
I wish I had read this before it happened as then it
could never have happened, right?

The point is, if you don't know why reverse isn't
working you propbably shouldn't be driving it - and
that part is opinion. The other part was fact. -BaH

